It'd be nice to get a mailing list account from PSF. Recently ChiPy has gone through a lot of formalization with its structure. Many members of the group mistook the chicago@python.org mailing list as an endorsement of the group by the PSF. That isn't the case. But for launching a new group, having a pupy@python.org mailing list should help with establishing credibility with the Python community in the Puget Sound region.    
